                      <li><a href="http://www.amchp.org/Calendar/Webinars/ArchivedWebinars/Documents/Leading%20in%20Changing%20Times%203%20Points.docx" target="_blank">Part 1: 3 Point Summary </a></li>
                    </ul>
                    <h3>Part 2: Leading Change: The Challenge of Change</h3>
                    <p>The second conversation of this series was held on Wednesday, January 15th at 1:30 pm ET titled, Leading Change: The Challenge of Change. Valerie Ricker, Assistant Director for the Population Health Division at the Maine Center for Disease Control and Prevention has over 30 years of MCH experience and currently serves on AMCHP&rsquo;s board as the Secretary.  Ms. Ricker provided an overview of the key concept, leadership and change, followed by her personal experience in combining MCH with other programs into one department, as Maine has undergone a lot of change in recent years. </p>
                    <p>After viewing this event, participants will be able to:</p>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Learn six characteristics of effective change.</li>
                      <li>Understand the difference between managing and leading change.</li>
                      <li>Identify opportunities to support or lead change within their organization. </li>
                      <li>Identify opportunities to practice strategies shared in the webinar.</li>
                    </ul>
